The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning algorithms, specifically Deep Q-Network (DQN) and Deep Deterministic Policy Gradient (DDPG), in designing a personalized cancer chemotherapy schedule. This involves optimizing a complex and uncertain system, which is a common problem in fields such as robotics and control systems, falling under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), systems and control (cs.SY), computational engineering (cs.CE), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Among these, machine learning and artificial intelligence are the most likely sub-categories as they are directly related to the use of reinforcement learning algorithms.
